===message:Good question, Mayumi.  I think it's a combination of lots of things, from economics to personal choices.  I don't think there is anything wrong with a parent (man or woman) staying home to raise a child if that suits their situation.  You're right, as long as your family unit as a whole is happy, what difference does it make?  My mother worked when I was young and I went to day-care and pre-school, but I turned out okay.  I think it depends on the time you actually do spend with your parent, whether that be all day or 5-6 hours a day. Use your time wisely!  I do not feel like I was raised by strangers, but I understand some people do.  All people are different from one another and some people may react differently to situations.  Some may prosper if they stay home with mom or dad and some may prosper if they don't.  I'm curious:  how do you feel about children developing social skills if they are home all day with adults?  I know play groups are possible, but some parents do not participate in those.  What do you think can be alternatives for play groups?  Since you have two at home, I know you can probably offer some suggestions (in case I'm ever lucky enough to be a home-maker!).   :)
=========yorg=========
