===message:hi lindsay,
well as my kids teacher we also have weekly fieldtrips. we go to fernbank, we have an annual pass for stone mountain park which allows him to have access to the playground that's full of kids his age, the marina boat, the barn, the petting zoo. and we also go to story time at the library every other day, days that i don't have class :0) we eat lunch at mickey d's on these library days where he also gets social interaction along with all of the other children of stay at home mom's. so he has a social life. however when he starts first grade, he will be attending public school (hopefully we can get him in private school). i don't want to keep him from the social life that you get away from home. i want him to start establishing his own little ways, and start having little crushes on girls as he gets older. so i won't be homeschooling him throughout his entire schoolhood :0)but as for right now, he does get alot of social interaction. just this year we also started giving him slumber parties, well my husband says for little boys i'm suppose to refer to it as "sleep overs"...whatever. :0)
