===subject:Reply
===from:Al Desmond
===date:Sun Apr 20  2:12:33 2003
===message:I feel that thier are a number of reasons why thier are stay at home mothers or home makers.  Some of which you mentioned.  But what I have found is that many women use the daycare cost as thier prime reason.  I know a few mothers who do the home school ritual and in some cases the kids excell in areas but fail in other areas.  I feel that for a child to be well rounded that they need an interaction that most families cant give them.  Now most will say that thier kids play with other kids and that they get plenty of activities but what about the learning style from different people.  Now I am sure you are very inteligent but at some point you have to wonder how your child will react when he is placed out of the security of the home school.  What I have seen is that home school fails the learning curve.  With today's ever evolving technology thier is no real way home school can keep up unless those monies saved from daycare is spent in keeping the child and the parent updated with the requirments of some of the higher scholastic schools for the age of the child.  Many children are not truly on the level that they need to be on in some areas of learning.
=========yorg=========
