===subject:reply
===from:Brenda Miller
===date:Mon Apr 28 16:10:31 2003
===message:I too am a stay at home mother of a five year old and a four year old, but my children have attended pre-school three days a week since they were three.  My decision to stay home was based on the fact that I did not want to have to be away from my children all day long (purely selfish). Also, my husband's parents divorced when he was 2 years old and his mother always worked so he was very much in favor of my staying home with our children. It did take some sacrifices on our part due to losing one income, but we have found that for our family the sacrifices were well worth it.  I will tell you that I look forward to returning to the work force when I graduate in three years, which is the same time my youngest will be starting first grade.  I do enjoy my role as a stay at home mom, but I do not feel that it is what I was meant to do forever.  
